%N A002301 a(n) = n! / 3.
%C A002301 a(n) is the number of n-permutations having 1, 2 and 3 in the same cycle. - _Geoffrey Critzer_, Apr 26 2009
%C A002301 a(n) is the total number of 3-cycles in all n-permutations. - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jul 22 2009
%C A002301 a(n+1) is the number of local maxima summed over all partitions of length n where n>1. - _Michael Somos_, Jul 19 2012
%C A002301 For n>2, n!/3 is the number of lattice points in the open parallelepiped of the factoradic n-simplex.  See Remark 3.1 in the article by L. Solus below. - _Liam Solus_, Aug 23 2018
